post_text:
Attention Parents: If you have not filled out a free/reduced meal application, please do so TODAY. Online Free/Reduced Meal Applications are not available for parents/guardians to fill out for the 2020-2021 school year. It is especially important for all students (including those who are 100% virtual learning students) to have an application on file. Please visit www.winfield.k12.al.us/applynow to fill out your online applications.

The online method is the preferred way for you to fill out an application as it is the fastest way to get your application processed and the most confidential. Your child has received a paper copy on the first day of school. If you have already completed the online application you DO NOT have to fill out the paper application.

If your child received free/reduced meals last year, a new application must be completed each year.

If you should have questions about the Free and Reduced Meal Application, please contact Sandy McCaleb, CNP Director at smccaleb@winfield.k12.al.us or call 1-205-487-0228.

post_text: Great message for our staff from a tremendous young man.
shared_text:
Rashad Johnson
August 19 at 11:15 AM ¬∑

A Message to Teachers...

@winfieldcityschools Thank You for the opportunity.

1. Change is happening daily, trust your preparation in this season.
2. Find your why and let it push you as adversity strikes.
3. Transformational Teaching over Transactional.

Online Free and Reduced Meal Applications are available for parents/guardians to fill out for the 2020-2021 school year. It is especially important for all students (including those who are 100% virtual learning students) to have an application on file. Please visit http://www.winfield.k12.al.us/o/winfield/page/apply-now-free-reduced-application to fill out your online applications.

The online method is the preferred way for you to fill out an application as it is the fastest way to get your child application processed and the most confidential. Your child will receive a paper copy of the Free and Reduced Meal application in their back to school paperwork. If you have already completed the online application, you DO NOT have to fill out the paper application.

If you have questions about the Fee and Reduced meal Application, please contact CNP Director, Sandy McCaleb at 205-487-0228 or smccaleb@winfield.k12.al.us.

post_text:
The Alabama State Department of Education has partnered with the University of Alabama to conduct a statewide school technology survey. The purpose of this survey is to build a statewide repository detailing Internet connectivity and Internet-enabled digital device availability to inform decision makers as we expand remote learning capabilities and enhance high-quality instruction to students around the state.

Whether a student is attending school in a traditional classroom setting, virtually, or a blended version of traditional and virtual, it is important that we hear from parents across the state as the survey responses will impact our efforts to respond to ongoing changes relating to remote and blended learning options throughout our state. Please take a few moments to share and complete this statewide school technology survey. The deadline for completing the survey is Friday, July 31, 2020.
http://ow.ly/OFJB50AEdwa

post_text:
Two hundred and forty-two days, 98,614 math hours, 264,595 lessons completed, 8.2 million complex math problems solved, and the Year-End Alabama Math Cup has come to a close! Winfield Elementary School of Winfield City Schools is this year‚Äôs 2020 Alabama Math Cup State Champion! Congratulations! Your school is now etched in Imagine Math history!
Winfield Elementary will receive a $250 Amazon e-gift card and the Alabama Math Cup trophy!
Close on their heels was Midfield High School of Midfield City Schools that took home the second-place finish and Pollard McCall Junior High School of Escambia County Schools coming in third. Way to show your math muscle!

post_text: Parents due to the spread of the Corona Virus school will be closed until April the 6th.Teachers will not be sending any assignments and will not be preparing or releasing any work packets. There will be e-learning opportunities posted on the district website for parents that choose to use those and work with your children during this time off. Scholastic is also offering a three week free trial of resources and this will be posted on the web site as well. Spring picture packets can be mailed directly to Bill Miller or turned in upon return. All April field trips will be cancelled and may not be able to be made up. We will seek to relay information as we receive it moving forward.
